<h1>Tom Critchlow</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://tomcritchlow.com/now/">tomcritchlow.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Brooklyn
NY
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Freelance marketing & strategy consultant.  Founder, Fiercely Curious
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I help build and scale sustainable teams of good people do good things.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I love watching individuals grow and evolve and I love to coach people and teams as they grow professionally and personally. I believe everyone has potential.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
You get to choose who you surround yourself with. Choose those with good energy.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Essay: On the uses of a liberal education by Mark Edmundson, Earl Shorris Part 1: <a href="http://www.ljhammond.com/essay.htm">http://www.ljhammond.com/essay.htm</a> Part 2: <a href="http://harpers.org/archive/1997/09/ii-as-a-weapon-in-the-hands-of-the-restless-poor/?single=1">http://harpers.org/archive/1997/09/ii-as-a-weapon-in-the-hands-of-the-restless-poor/?single=1</a>
</p>

